Determine if the following statement is True or False:

A known error can be created when one or more of the following conditions is/are TRUE:

• The root cause has been identified.
• A workaround is known (better corrective action, or the one applied to resolve the error).
• A permanent fix has been identified but will have delayed implementation, and known risks resulting from the delayed implementation have been provided.
Select the best answer.


True

False
